      • COLLECTOR_URI

        public static final String COLLECTOR_URI
        The url and port number for the Splunk HEC endpoint or load balancer in front of Splunk cluster. Can also be a comma-separated list of urls. Example: https://127.0.0.1:8088
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DISABLE_CERT_VALIDATION

        public static final String DISABLE_CERT_VALIDATION
        If true, disables certificate validation and allows sending to non-https endpoints. Defaults to false.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CHANNELS_PER_DESTINATION

        public static final String CHANNELS_PER_DESTINATION
        Integer number of channels per internet socket address destination. Event batches are load balanced across all channels. (Note that a single URL may resolve to multiple destinations based on DNS lookup).
        See Also:
        MOCK_FORCE_URL_MAP_TO_ONE, DEFAULT_CHANNELS_PER_DESTINATION, Constant Field Values

      • MOCK_HTTP_KEY

        public static final String MOCK_HTTP_KEY
        If true, uses a mock HEC instead of a live Splunk instance. Useful for running unit tests without a live Splunk instance.
        See Also:
        MOCK_HTTP_CLASSNAME, Constant Field Values

      • MOCK_FORCE_URL_MAP_TO_ONE

        public static final String MOCK_FORCE_URL_MAP_TO_ONE
        If true, forces each url in COLLECTOR_URI to map to only a single internet socket address during DNS resolution. Defaults to false.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • UNRESPONSIVE_MS

        public static final String UNRESPONSIVE_MS
        If a channel is unresponsive (no ack's received) for this many ms, the channel is declared dead. A replacement channel is created, and all unacked messages from the dead channel are re-sent on the replacement channel.
        See Also:
        RETRIES, DEFAULT_UNRESPONSIVE_MS, Constant Field Values

      • MAX_TOTAL_CHANNELS

        public static final String MAX_TOTAL_CHANNELS
        Integer that caps the total number of channels across all destinations.
        See Also:
        CHANNELS_PER_DESTINATION, DEFAULT_MAX_TOTAL_CHANNELS, Constant Field Values

      • MAX_UNACKED_EVENT_BATCHES_PER_CHANNEL

        public static final String MAX_UNACKED_EVENT_BATCHES_PER_CHANNEL
        Integer that caps the total number of unacknowledged event batches per channel. If the cap is reached, the channel will be considered "full" and no more events will be sent through it until it receives acknowledgements from Splunk.
        See Also:
        DEFAULT_MAX_UNACKED_EVENT_BATCHES_PER_CHANNEL, MIN_UNACKED_EVENT_BATCHES_PER_CHANNEL, Constant Field Values

      • EVENT_BATCH_SIZE

        public static final String EVENT_BATCH_SIZE
        Character length of the internal buffer that fills up as Events are passed into the client. When full, the buffer is flushed and events are sent to Splunk HEC.
        See Also:
        DEFAULT_EVENT_BATCH_SIZE, MIN_EVENT_BATCH_SIZE, Constant Field Values

      • ACK_POLL_MS

        public static final String ACK_POLL_MS

        See Also:

      • HEALTH_POLL_MS

        public static final String HEALTH_POLL_MS

        public static final String BLOCKING_TIMEOUT_MS

      • MIN_UNACKED_EVENT_BATCHES_PER_CHANNEL

        public static final int MIN_UNACKED_EVENT_BATCHES_PER_CHANNEL
        Minimum value for MAX_UNACKED_EVENT_BATCHES_PER_CHANNEL property. At 1, every event batch post must wait for the ack to come back before another event batch can be posted. Therefore, at 1, there is no pipelining of event posts, and efficiency will be low.
        See Also:
        MAX_UNACKED_EVENT_BATCHES_PER_CHANNEL, Constant Field Values
